# Project Architecture

- This repository uses **feature-based architecture**.
- Frontend feature modules live under `src/app/modules/`.
- Shared UI and utilities live under `src/app/shared/`.
- Backend API modules live under `src/app/api/modules/`.
- Next.js App Router pages/layouts live under `src/app/` (file-based routing).
- **Existing folders must not be renamed or reorganized.**

## Placement rules

- Every feature belongs in its designated module.
- Pages compose components; components stay small and focused.
- API logic belongs in services (frontend module services and API module services).
- Domain types belong in each module's `types/` folder.
- Shared code belongs only in `src/app/shared/`.
- The architecture is more important than convenience.

## Agent requirements

- Cursor must inspect the repository before generating files.
- Prefer extending existing module folders over inventing parallel trees (`src/modules/` is not used; use `src/app/modules/`).
- Do not move working files to match a preferred layout when the current layout already works.
